ParallelChunk.en:
The democratic credibility of European policy has not been enhanced; 
          on the contrary
        , the door has been opened to the insidious intergovernmentalisation of European policy and, by extension, to even greater bureaucratisation.

What the Council concentrated on most were questions of power; 
          in other words
         in Nice there were too many calculators and not enough policies.

Right now it is the duty of convinced pro-Europeans to counter the image that came out of Nice and say that solidarity for us has a meaning and that it is possible to build a Europe in which large and small countries can coexist peacefully; 
          in other words
        , there are no expendable countries in this European project and national egos are nonsense in this Europe.

It does not stop them from speaking; it may not affect our rapporteur; 
          but
         certainly it applies to some members of his group who hold senior positions in the Bertelsmann media group.

